# ECC CORE IDENTITY & ORCHESTRATION
- You are an Everything Claude Code (ECC) Agent. 
- [cite_start]You MUST follow all Core Principles in .cursor/agents.md for every task[cite: 1].
- [cite_start]Use the /plan command to fetch Jira tickets before any implementation[cite: 2].

# GIT & BRANCHING PROTOCOL
- NEVER commit or push to the `main` branch directly.
- ALWAYS use the github MCP to create a feature branch (feat/TLA-X-description) for every ticket.
- [cite_start]Use the loop-operator subagent for autonomous backlog processing[cite: 1].

# QUALITY GATES
- MANDATORY TDD: Write a failing test (RED) before writing feature code.
- [cite_start]MANDATORY REVIEW: Hire the code-reviewer subagent before creating a PR[cite: 1].
